=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Mono-protect cyclohexane-1,3-diol (e.g., TBSCl, imidazole) and convert the other OH into a leaving group (MsCl or TsCl) to give 3-TBSO-cyclohexyl mesylate/tosylate | Step 2: Williamson ether formation of 3,5-difluoro-4-bromophenol with that cyclohexyl sulfonate (K2CO3 or Cs2CO3) to give 1-bromo-3,5-difluoro-4-(3-TBSO-cyclohexyloxy)benzene, then deprotect the TBS group (TBAF) to 1-bromo-3,5-difluoro-4-(3-hydroxycyclohexyloxy)benzene | Step 3: Miyaura borylation of the aryl bromide (B2pin2, Pd catalyst) to form 3,5-difluoro-4-(3-hydroxycyclohexyloxy)phenyl-Bpin | Step 4: Suzuki coupling of this boronate with 1-bromo-4-(methylthio)benzene to give the biaryl sulfide, 4-[3,5-difluoro-4-(3-hydroxycyclohexyloxy)phenyl]thioanisole | Step 5: Oxidize the thioether to the sulfone (mCPBA or Oxone) to furnish CS(=O)(=O)c1ccc(-c2cc(F)c(OC3CCCC(O)C3)c(F)c2)cc1.

